Recurly Coding exercise round (due 3/7/2016)
Kevin R. Emery (fulvius@gmail.com)

This example is intended to run in a *nix compatible shell
Install Ruby (> 1.9) and RubyGems
Then, from the 'recurly' directory 
  gem install bundler
  bundle install

to run all tests from the 'recurly' directory:
./run_examples.sh

To run the UI Automation from the 'selenium' directory:
rspec spec/views/accounts.rb

To run API automation from the 'api_tests' directory:
rspec recurly_accounts_api.rb

Acknowledgements:
https://robots.thoughtbot.com/how-we-test-rails-applications
